4 NEW SUBSECTION. 10. All orders relating to custody of a
5 child shall specify the rights and responsibilities of each
6 parent relative to the minor child’s educational setting.
7 The order shall, at a minimum, specify a parent’s rights
8 and responsibilities regarding physical access to the child
9 during the school day; access to records involving the health,
10 education, and welfare of the child; decision-making authority
11 including instances when parental consent or authorization is
12 required; and the removal of the child from the premises of the
13 educational setting during school hours. However, the order
14 shall not require that a parent have physical access to a child
15 during the school day or be allowed to remove the child from
16 the premises of the educational setting during school hours
17 if the child is being provided competent private instruction
18 or independent private instruction in the home of the other
19 parent in accordance with chapter 299A. This exception shall
20 not apply to competent private instruction or independent
21 private instruction being given at a location outside the home
22 of either parent. Any parent with legal custody of the child
23 shall provide a copy of the order to the educational setting
24 and to the school district of the child to whom the order
